<task id="010" project="agent-framework-knowledge-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Create .claude/skills/agent-framework-component/SKILL.md</title>
    <phase>5</phase>
    <tags>knowledge-base, agent-framework, skill, claude-config</tags>
    <estimate>1h</estimate>
    <status>pending</status>
    <parallel-group>—</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>009</dependencies>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    <goal>Create .claude/skills/agent-framework-component/SKILL.md modeled on .claude/skills/fluent-v9-component/SKILL.md. This is the user-facing skill that triggers loading of the patterns + knowledge/agent-framework/ NOTES + relevant docs when Claude detects Agent Framework work. Without this skill, the knowledge base sits unused — the skill is the activation surface.</goal>
    <context>fluent-v9-component is the proven template. It declares frontmatter (description / tags / techStack / appliesTo / alwaysApply), has Purpose / Applies When / Workflow (Step 0 intent routing → Step 1 knowledge load → Step 2 ADR contracts → Step 3 code review checklist → Step 4 verify before claiming done) / Related skills / Related references sections. The new skill mirrors this for Agent Framework: intent-routing table maps tasks (new agent / new tool / new middleware / observability / agent-vs-workflow decision) to pattern files, ADRs are ADR-013 + (anchor only) ADR-001 ADR-028 bff-extensions.md constraint.</context>
    <constraints>
      - MAIN SESSION ONLY — .claude/ write boundary applies (root CLAUDE.md §3)
      - Frontmatter MUST match the format of other skills (.claude/skills/fluent-v9-component/SKILL.md is the canonical example)
      - `appliesTo` globs: target src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/ + Spaarke.Core AI surfaces; do NOT over-target (e.g., do NOT match all .cs in the BFF — only Services/Ai/)
      - `tags` include: ai, agent-framework, dotnet, ichatclient, middleware, openai
      - Workflow Step 0 routing table maps user intent → pattern files to load (mirrors fluent-v9-component Step 0)
      - Workflow Step 1 mandatory load list: knowledge/agent-framework/NOTES.md FIRST, then the intent-specific patterns, then drill into docs/ only if a pattern punts there with `→`
      - Workflow Step 2 ADR application: ADR-013 (PublicContracts/ facade for CRUD→AI) + .claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md (BFF-extension governance before adding new endpoints/services)
      - Workflow Step 3 code review checklist: 8-10 items targeting the specific drift risks (e.g., "ChatMessage namespace alias used when both Models.Ai.Chat and Microsoft.Extensions.AI imported", "AIFunctionFactory.Create with [Description] not raw delegates", "Middleware composition order: telemetry outermost", "UseFunctionInvocation vs raw client for compound intent detection")
      - Workflow Step 4: explicit "test in BFF integration env" requirement; do not claim done after only `dotnet build`
      - Total length 100-150 lines — matches fluent-v9-component scope
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/skills/fluent-v9-component/SKILL.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/ai/INDEX.md</file>
      <file>knowledge/agent-framework/NOTES.md</file>
