    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Read .claude/skills/fluent-v9-component/SKILL.md as the template</step>
    <step>Read .claude/patterns/ai/INDEX.md (created by task 009) to inventory pattern files the skill will reference</step>
    <step>Read knowledge/agent-framework/NOTES.md (rewritten by task 007) to confirm the §1/§2 structure the skill will load</step>
    <step>Draft frontmatter: description (1 sentence, plain English — what the skill does); tags (ai, agent-framework, dotnet, ichatclient, middleware, openai); techStack (dotnet-8, agent-framework, microsoft-extensions-ai, azure-openai); appliesTo globs (target Services/Ai/ paths only); alwaysApply: false</step>
    <step>Draft Purpose section — explain why this skill exists (anchor every Agent Framework component task in Spaarke patterns + the live Microsoft reference)</step>
    <step>Draft Applies When section — list intent triggers ("Creating or modifying a chat agent in Services/Ai/Chat/", "Editing IChatClient middleware", etc.) AND explicit NOT-applicable list (NOT for JPS playbook authoring → jps-action-create; NOT for Foundry Agent Service → foundry-agent skill)</step>
    <step>Draft Workflow Step 0 — intent routing table mapping user intent to pattern files</step>
    <step>Draft Workflow Step 1 — knowledge load order: NOTES.md first, then patterns, then docs/* only if `→` punts there</step>
    <step>Draft Workflow Step 2 — ADR contracts: ADR-013 PublicContracts/ facade requirement + bff-extensions.md governance + (cite) ADR-028 for managed-identity credential choice</step>
    <step>Draft Workflow Step 3 — code review checklist with 8-10 Spaarke-specific items (drift-targeted)</step>
    <step>Draft Workflow Step 4 — verification standard: explicit "integration test in BFF env" requirement for changes touching middleware or tool registration</step>
    <step>Draft Related skills + Related references sections</step>
    <step>Write to .claude/skills/agent-framework-component/SKILL.md</step>
    <step>Commit: `feat(skills): add agent-framework-component SKILL.md (R1 task 010)`</step>
  </steps>
  <tools>
    <tool>Read</tool>
    <tool>Glob</tool>
    <tool>Write</tool>
    <tool>Skill(task-execute)</tool>
  </tools>
  <outputs>
    <output>.claude/skills/agent-framework-component/SKILL.md</output>
  </outputs>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>SKILL.md exists at .claude/skills/agent-framework-component/SKILL.md</criterion>
